just_use events.go

# label: CANONICAL
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Per-user event queue, long-poll delivery. Two push modes: PushToAll
(already-authorized events like flag updates) vs PushFiltered (channel-
scoped — caller supplies a predicate on the queue owner's userID).

**Buried history.** We no longer synthesize heartbeat events in the long-
poll timeout path: the heartbeat used lastEventID+1, colliding with the ID
the next real event would get from q.lastID++. Client advanced past that
ID and silently skipped the real event. Return empty pending instead; the
client re-polls on its own cadence.

Reaper removes queues idle past timeout (Cat crashes, tab closes).
createdAt is the fallback lastActivity so brand-new queues get a grace
period before their first poll.
